channel.title: This May Seem Noobish...But I've Always Wondered
channel.description: I've always wondered, what makes java coding work? I mean, was it pre-written somewhere in the books of life, and humans just discovered it? I'm just taking a shot in the dark, but seriously, how does java coding work? I would like to know =] Is there like java coding within java coding? o.O thanks...lol, I was bored and wanted to know

@Zenzie wrote:

Actually java exist when it was called to another weird name they started to write it and suddenly when they took a break some guy came up in the coffee room [Logo] with the name so they called it Java ! You start writing java in files as the compiler converts it via the JVM in class files … When you press RUN the mahcine activates and all sorts computers can use it , MAC , WINDOWS , LINUX , …
